The paper discusses the design and implementation of an artificial-intelligence-powered robotic assistant for the physically impaired, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of neural network architectures for specific modular components of the system indicates the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on assisting individuals with physical impairments suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. The use of object detection and natural language understanding also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) involvement.
